The article discusses President Obama's commitment to restoring fairness to the tax code and providing tax relief to working Americans. It highlights the measures taken by the Obama Administration to give tax cuts to Americans in need while jump-starting growth and job creation. The article mentions the Making Work Pay tax credit, which provides a refundable tax credit of up to $400 for working individuals and $800 for working households. Other measures mentioned include the expansion of the First-Time Homebuyer tax credit, the increased Earned Income Tax Credit, the American Opportunity Tax Credit, the Child Tax Credit Expansion, and the health insurance subsidy for workers between jobs. The article also mentions benefits for retirees, other Social Security beneficiaries, and disabled veterans, as well as tax deductions for auto sales and excise taxes and the carryback of net operating losses for small businesses. It concludes by providing examples of how these tax cuts affect different American families.